
I created my Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic using Canva, which is a free and easy-to-use online design tool.
The infographic is designed to help students understand the importance of digital literacy in today’s academic and professional environment.
The design explains what digital literacy means and how students can use technology responsibly and effectively. 
It includes sections on useful digital tools such as Google Docs, Google Drive, and Zoom, which help students collaborate, store files, and attend online classes. 
The infographic also highlights safe internet practices like using strong passwords, avoiding suspicious links, and protecting personal information online. 
In addition, it includes tips for maintaining a professional online presence and proper email etiquette.
While creating this design, one interesting aspect was learning how to organize information visually so that it is easy to understand.
The most difficult part was selecting the right icons, colors, and layout to make the infographic both attractive and informative. Overall,
this activity helped me understand how visual communication can effectively spread digital awareness among students.
